The paper discusses the performance comparison of different virtualization technologies in terms of power consumption, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also evaluates the network performance of these technologies, which relates to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the characteristics of hypervisor-based and container-based virtualization, which falls under the Operating Systems (cs.OS) category. The investigation of how these technologies react to particular workloads also relates to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper presents empirical results, which falls under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category.
